ill holpe up, that are mar|ried
to one another, and
not maried to CHRIST.</P>
<P>Beauty is as it hits, if
the <HI>heart</HI> do not answere
the <HI>face,</HI> it were better
missed, it will proove a
<HI>snare</HI> which was an <HI>orna|ment:</HI>
the more any have
of this, the more cause
they have to pray, <HI>Leade
us not into temptation.</HI></P>
<P><PB N="67" REF="37">
Earth is a place of <HI>pe|nance;</HI>
and <HI>small drinke</HI>
and <HI>Camells haire</HI> doth
well; tis a place of toile
and labour, and men goe
not to worke in their <HI>best
cloathes:</HI> Men should do
