their insides a little bet|ter,
and let the bodie
shift: I never heard any
man found fault with for
his ragges, I heare it up|braided
to one, that hee
went in <HI>purple.</HI></P>
<P>It is not our meanes,
but our sinnes that shuts
us out from God; I will
<PB N="68" REF="38">
be asham'd of nothing
but my sinnes, and proud
of nothing but that I am
a Christian.</P>
<P>I will never care what
I am in mens eyes, but in
Gods: Beautie, Wealth,
Honour, may make us
accepted of men, but 'tis
onely a broken heart can
doe the deed with God:
never any man came to
Heaven for his good
lookes.</P>
<P>Hee is not a Iew that
is so outwardly, then had
not <HI>Hlerusalem</HI> fallen:
nor he an Apostle, that
<PB N="69" REF="38">
doth so professe it, then
