will He not do where He
loves? Oh <HI>God,</HI> they
<PB N="71" REF="39">
doe not <HI>know</HI> thee that
<HI>distrust</HI> thee.</P>
<P>To give with hope to
<HI>receive,</HI> is to <HI>lend</HI> and not
to give: or rather to <HI>put
to use</HI> and not to <HI>lend:</HI> I
will give where I cannot
be <HI>requited,</HI> so shall my
<HI>reward</HI> be in <HI>Heaven.</HI></P>
<P><HI>Charitie</HI> is of that which
a man hath, and not of
that a man hath not: If
the purse will not reach
to a <HI>Sepulcher</HI> with that
Counseller of <HI>Arimathea,</HI>
