<PB N="116" REF="62">
of <HI>piety,</HI> not of <HI>fashions.</HI>
I will never be niggardly
of another mans purse,
deny my selfe that which
God hath not.</P>
<P>There may be pride
in the meanest things in
the world; no lesse the
<HI>Cynick</HI> of his <HI>tub,</HI> than
<HI>Alexander</HI> of all the <HI>world</HI>
besides: <HI>Sackcloth</HI> and
Ashes in the same bill
