another; it is not for no|thing
(I have thought) that
he is painted with a clove~
foote, hee loves <HI>divisions</HI>
so well, and there is no
greater argument of a di|vell
incarnate than a ma|licious
heart: say what
thou wilt, but I will ne|ver
beleeve thee against
scripture, that thou lovest
God whom thou hast
not seene, that lovest not
thy brother whom thou
<PB N="152" REF="80">
hast seene; if wee love
Him we will love one a|nother.</P>
<P>If we will be <HI>Christs</HI>
Disciples we must leave
all, but its not all, wee
must take up our crosse
